      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Anguish at Gracie Mansion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Christopher Carolin letter on May 11 article on New York City Mayor Rudolph Giuliani's marital separation says fact that Giuliani has put so human a face on his situation is compelling; expresses hope that he stays in politics</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Giuliani and His Wife of 16 Years Are Separating'' (front page, May 11): The fact that Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani has put so human a face on his current situation is compelling. There is an obvious edge gone from his voice and his face. Such tragedy, and yet he is infinitely more appealing for the way he has reacted. Let's hope that the price he pays for this dose of wisdom isn't too steep and he stays in politics.</p>
        <p>CHRISTOPHER CAROLIN  Lake Forest, Ill., May 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
